## PRE-FLIGHT SAFETY CHECK (DO THIS FIRST — STOP IF ANY CHECK FAILS)

Before making any changes to any file, perform every one of the following checks. If **any single check fails**, stop immediately and report which check failed and why. Do not proceed.

1. **Repo URL check** — Confirm the repository URL is exactly: `https://github.com/paananiruddh/masready`. Do not operate on `softwarecomparereview/masready` or any other fork.
2. **Branch check** — Confirm the active branch is `main`. Do not operate on any other branch without explicit user instruction.
3. **CNAME check** — Confirm the `CNAME` file at the repo root reads exactly: `masready.com.au`. This repository powers the public marketing site at masready.com.au. The CNAME file must not be altered.
4. **Live demo app separation check** — Confirm that `mas9power.masready.com.au` is a **separate, private Replit deployment** (`replit.com/@aniruddhpan/Maximo-Bro-Bot`). Do not edit that app in this session. Changes to the private live app are out of scope here and must be applied separately.
5. **Skill-packs directory check** — Confirm `workspace/system/skill-packs/` exists in the repository. **DO NOT RENAME THIS DIRECTORY.** It is the runtime skill module registry. Renaming it will break the live platform.
6. **Knowledge-base directory check** — Confirm `workspace/system/maximo-knowledge-base/` exists in the repository. **DO NOT RENAME THIS DIRECTORY.** It is the static Markdown knowledge base. Renaming it will break the live platform.
7. **Single-repo guard** — Confirm you will only edit files inside `paananiruddh/masready` during this session. Do not open, read, or write to any other repository.
8. **No live API overclaiming** — Do not introduce or restore any copy, UI label, tooltip, schema.org claim, or comment that asserts a live API integration exists unless the corresponding implementation is present and tested in this repository.

