## PART 1: SKILL COVERAGE CORRECTION — LAYERED BOT MODEL

### 1.1 — Remove all HR/people/team skill wording

Search every file in the repository for the phrases listed below. Remove or replace each occurrence per the rules in sections 1.2 and 1.3. The files where these phrases are most likely to appear are:

- `artifacts/masready/src/pages/features.tsx`
- `artifacts/masready/src/pages/mas9-power.tsx`
- `artifacts/masready/src/pages/home.tsx`
- `artifacts/masready/src/pages/demo-walkthrough.tsx`
- Any other `.tsx`, `.ts`, `.html`, or `.md` file returned by a case-insensitive search for "skill coverage"

Phrases to remove entirely (zero occurrences permitted in any public-facing file after this change):

- "team skills"
- "people skills" (when adjacent to skill coverage metrics)
- "resource gap" (when adjacent to skill coverage metrics)
- "contractor uplift" (when adjacent to skill coverage metrics)
- Any sentence that reads as though "82% skill coverage" measures human staffing, team capability, or headcount adequacy

### 1.2 — Exact before/after copy replacements

Apply these substitutions wherever the original text appears, including in JSX strings, template literals, HTML attribute values, and comments:

| Before | After |
|---|---|
| `82% skill coverage` | `82% bot skill-pack coverage across Maximo delivery domains (system-defined — base packs)` |
| `skill coverage` (standalone label or heading) | `Bot Skill-Pack Coverage` |
| `team skills` | *(remove entirely — do not substitute)* |
| `people skills` (adjacent to coverage metric) | *(remove entirely — do not substitute)* |
| `resource gap` (adjacent to coverage metric) | *(remove entirely — do not substitute)* |
| `contractor uplift` (adjacent to coverage metric) | *(remove entirely — do not substitute)* |

### 1.3 — Update /skills page description

Locate the description string rendered on the `/skills` page (likely in `artifacts/masready/src/pages/skills.tsx` or the corresponding route component). Replace the existing description with:

