```

### 1.4 — Add 5-layer model explanation to /skills page

Add a collapsible or static section to the `/skills` page (or a `SkillLayerModel` component imported by that page) that explains the five-layer architecture. The rendered text must be:

---

**How Skill Packs Are Organised**

MASReady uses a five-layer model to separate static knowledge from customer-specific evidence:

| Layer | Type | Key | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| Layer 1 | Base Maximo Knowledge Skill Packs | `base_maximo_skill_pack` | Ships with MASReady core. Offline-capable. No customer data required. |
| Layer 2 | Customer Evidence Packs | `customer_evidence_pack` | Approved evidence inputs. Customer approval mandatory before ingestion. |
| Layer 3 | Customer-Specific Skill Pack Overlays | `customer_skill_overlay` | Generated from customer evidence. Deployed inside the customer boundary only. |
| Layer 4 | Runtime Product Skills | `runtime_product_skill` | Generate review-ready outputs from available evidence at runtime. |
| Layer 5 | Future Skills | `future_skill_pack` | Roadmap only — not yet available. |

---

This table must be visible without authentication (it describes the system model, not customer data). Do not gate it behind any auth check.

