### 6.5 — Add persona section to home.tsx

In `artifacts/masready/src/pages/home.tsx`, add a new section with the heading **"Built for your team"** after the existing feature highlights and before the footer/CTA section. The section must include one card or list entry for each of the following six roles:

---

**Delivery Manager**
*"How confident am I in this delivery? What evidence do I have?"*
MASReady aggregates bot-generated delivery intelligence into a single review-ready view — so you can walk into a steering committee with evidence, not estimates.

---

**Maximo Administrator**
*"Which parts of the Maximo configuration have we actually validated?"*
MASReady maps installed bot skill packs against your Maximo configuration fingerprint, showing exactly what has been assessed and what hasn't.

---

**Solution Architect**
*"Where are the integration gaps between our current Maximo and the MAS 9 target?"*
MASReady's layered skill-pack model cross-references your as-is configuration against the upgrade target, surfacing gaps the bot has evidence for and flagging what still needs assessment.

---

**Security / Governance Lead**
*"Can I prove that no unapproved data left the customer boundary?"*
MASReady's zero-trust governance log records every evidence ingestion event, approval action, and export — providing an auditable chain of custody.

---

**Business Analyst**
*"What Maximo functional areas are covered by the current delivery scope?"*
MASReady skill-pack coverage maps directly to Maximo functional domains — so scope decisions are grounded in what the bot has actually assessed.

---

**IT Asset Manager**
*"What is our licence exposure going into the MAS 9 upgrade?"*
MASReady's licence planning view surfaces Maximo licence consumption patterns from available evidence — for planning purposes, not IBM-certified advice.

---

Each card must use bot-capability framing, not people-skills framing. Do not use phrases like "your team's skill level" or "staff capability" in this section.

### 6.6 — Add "Two paths in. Same intelligence out." to features.tsx

In `artifacts/masready/src/pages/features.tsx`, add a new section with the heading **"Two paths in. Same intelligence out."** Place it in a logical position within the page (after the core feature list, before any pricing or CTA section).

The section content must be:

---

**API Mode**
MASReady connects directly to the IBM Maximo API using tenant credentials. Bot skill packs query live Maximo data to generate review-ready outputs in real time. Requires Maximo API access and configured environment variables.

**Extract Mode**
For environments where live API access is not available or approved, MASReady accepts structured data extracts. The same bot skill packs run against the extract, producing equivalent review-ready outputs. No live Maximo connection required.

Both modes produce the same delivery intelligence outputs. The difference is the data path — not the quality of the assessment.

---

Do not claim that both modes are currently fully implemented in the live application unless you can verify that in the codebase. If only one mode is implemented, say: "API Mode is available today. Extract Mode is on the roadmap."

