## PART 10: REMAINING RISKS AND UNRESOLVED ITEMS

The following items are **not resolved by this prompt**. They require separate action on the private live application or are blocked pending external input. Record these in your post-implementation report.

1. **P0 — Live app auth gap (CRITICAL):** The `requirePlatformAdmin` middleware created in section 5.1 is a public-repo stub only. The unauthenticated `/api/audit` and `/api/customers` endpoints on the **live private app** at `replit.com/@aniruddhpan/Maximo-Bro-Bot` remain exposed until that deployment is separately patched. This is the highest-priority unresolved security issue.

2. **P0 — Real PII in live audit log:** Until the live app is patched, the `/api/audit` endpoint on `mas9power.masready.com.au` exposes real user activity, real tenant identifiers, and potentially real PII. This cannot be fixed by changes to the public repo.

3. **P1 — Real customer tenants visible in live platform-admin view:** Bureau of Meteorology, and any other real customer tenants, remain visible in the live platform-admin tenant list until the private app is patched and live data is sanitised or migrated.

4. **P2 — "Assetize" internal brand in live app audit log messages:** Audit log messages in the live app may reference the internal brand name. These must be updated in the private app deployment separately.

5. **P2 — "Maximo Bro Bot" title in live app UI:** The live application at `mas9power.masready.com.au` may still display "Maximo Bro Bot" in the browser title, navigation, or footer. This requires a separate deployment update to the private Replit app.

6. **P2 — `aseeti-theme` localStorage key in live app:** The live app uses a localStorage key that may expose an internal brand codename. This requires a migration in the private app (with a localStorage key migration to avoid breaking existing sessions).

7. **P3 — Mermaid diagram syntax validation:** After replacing `<pre class="diagram">` with `<pre class="mermaid">`, each diagram's content must be validated against Mermaid syntax. Invalid syntax will cause diagrams to fail silently. Validate each diagram manually in the Mermaid Live Editor (`https://mermaid.live`) after replacement.

8. **P3 — Customer evidence ingestion pipeline (Layer 2/3) not yet built:** The five-layer model documented in section 1.4 describes Layer 2 (Customer Evidence Packs) and Layer 3 (Customer-Specific Skill Pack Overlays) as functional layers. The ingestion pipeline that accepts, approves, and deploys these layers is not yet present in either the public repo or the private live app.

9. **P3 — Evidence pack generator routes exist but generator code is absent:** Route stubs for evidence pack generation exist in the codebase, but the generator implementation is not visible in the public repo. These routes should return `501 Not Implemented` until the generator is built.

10. **P4 — Report and runbook generation is roadmap:** Any UI element or copy that implies automated runbook or report generation is available today should be updated to say "planned" or "roadmap". The routes exist; the generator is future work.

